      "comment": "SHAUN LEE ROSE (8) showed little early speed at his last couple, the latest finishing fourth (25.33) in a Grade 5 at this track. Solid record here at the distance winning seven races. Can discover winning form. ROYAL PRIDE (3) was never in contention last time after drifting back at Warragul, but prior to that won by 0.6 lengths at this track (24.81) beating Yorkshire Girl in a Grade 5 on April 15. Comes through a solid form race last start. Has ability and is one of the better chances. SASSY GAL (6) is better than last start when fifth (24.91) from Box 8 at this track over 435m. Has a solid record from this box including two wins and a minor placing. Can figure in the finish. QUICK RESPONSE (4) will give backers a sight.",
